# Folder Structure & File Placement

## The Map

```
src/
├── app/              ← Routing ONLY. No logic, no data, minimal JSX
├── components/       ← Shared UI used across 2+ UNRELATED pages
│   ├── layout/       ← Navbar, Footer, TopBar (shell components)
│   ├── ui/           ← Primitive reusables: Button, Card, Accordion...
│   └── sections/     ← Full sections reused verbatim on 2+ pages
├── features/         ← Page-private components (used by ONE page only)
│   ├── home/
│   ├── about/
│   ├── products/
│   ├── product-detail/
│   ├── services/
│   ├── service-detail/
│   ├── industries/distribution-grid/
│   ├── solutions/software-application/
│   └── contact/
├── lib/              ← Pure JS logic — NO React, NO JSX
│   ├── data/         ← Static data arrays (products, services, faqs...)
│   ├── api/          ← Async server fetchers (server-only)
│   ├── utils/        ← Pure functions (cn, formatDate, validators...)
│   └── validations/  ← Zod schemas
├── hooks/            ← Custom React hooks (client-side only)
├── config/           ← App constants (routes.js, site.js) — no secrets
└── styles/           ← globals.css only
```

## Decision Rules

### Where does a new component go?

Ask: "Is this used on more than one unrelated page?"
- **YES** → `src/components/ui/ComponentName/ComponentName.jsx`
- **NO** → `src/features/[page-name]/ComponentName.jsx`

Ask: "Is this a Navbar / Footer / TopBar shell?"
- **YES** → `src/components/layout/ComponentName/`

Ask: "Is it a full section used verbatim on 2+ pages?"
- **YES** → `src/components/sections/SectionName/`

### Where does new data go?
- Static arrays, objects, constants → `src/lib/data/filename.js`
- NEVER define data arrays inside a component file

### Where does a new utility function go?
- `src/lib/utils/` — pure JS, no React imports allowed in this folder

### Where does a new async fetcher go?
- `src/lib/api/filename.js` — must start with `import 'server-only'`

### Where does a new custom hook go?
- `src/hooks/useHookName.js`

## Naming Conventions
| Item | Convention | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Component files | PascalCase | `ProductCard.jsx` |
| Component folders | PascalCase | `ProductCard/` |
| Data files | camelCase | `products.js` |
| Util files | camelCase | `formatDate.js` |
| Hook files | camelCase prefixed with `use` | `useScrollPosition.js` |
| API route files | always `route.js` | `app/api/contact/route.js` |
| Page files | always `page.jsx` | `app/(marketing)/about/page.jsx` |
| Barrel files | always `index.js` | `components/ui/Button/index.js` |

## Barrel Export Pattern
Every folder under `components/ui/` and `components/sections/` must have an `index.js`:

```js
// src/components/ui/Button/index.js
export { default } from './Button'
export { Button } from './Button'
```
